adviseScripts.text: There you are, Handsome.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Now that you're here, let's kick out the jams.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Red Hood presses play on her cassette player.
Da dada♪
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Aren't you sick of this song by now?
Hum along to the song with Red Hood.
This isn't just some ordinary song.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: This is a record of my life.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Listen to it carefully.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Wow, you've memorized the melody that quickly?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: You just made my day.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Oooh, my favorite part is coming up!
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: La de da♪
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Red Hood and I listen intently to the music together.
Which do you think is more important:
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: the past or the future?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: The past.
The future.
It makes sense that you'd pick that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: That's fine, so long as you don't allow it to constrain you in the present.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: After all, the past should remain in the past.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Ah, you truly are a wonderful specimen,
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: both physically and mentally.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: I hope you can always boldly go forth with your head held high, looking towards the future.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Discussed the past and future with Red Hood for a while.
You know what?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: I kinda miss...
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Me?
Your friends from before?
Pssh.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: You're nothing if not confident.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: It's no wonder why Rapi had such feelings for you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Ha ha.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Come on.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Try and have a little tact.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: In situations like this, you should feign ignorance.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Discussed some easier topics with Red Hood for a while.
I'm bored out of my gourd.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Waddya say you and I get frisky?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Er, isn't that a bit...
I'm down.
I'm only joking.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: You remind me of a friend I had a long time ago.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Man, the fun I had teasing her...
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: ... I wonder how she's doing right about now?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: I'm only joking.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: If I laid a finger on you, Rapi would never let me hear the end of it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: I may be many things, but disloyal is not one of them.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Red Hood and I have a pleasant chat.
Hey, Handsome.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: What do you think is the most important quality of a good Commander?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Leadership, naturally.
A sense of humor, I guess?
A textbook answer, but nothing more than that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: My former boss would have never given such a dry answer.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Ha! That's a new one.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: If my former boss was still alive,
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: you and he would get along like a house on fire.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Red Hood and I discuss the qualities a commander should possess.
Sometimes, I have this nagging feeling...
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: What kind of feeling?
My time has already come and gone,
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: and yet, I still exist in this world.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: It's a strange thought, and whenever it pops up in my mind, I'm a bit unsettled.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: I think that's a perfectly normal reaction.
Shouldn't you be excited at having a new lease on life?
Yeah? I thought you'd be weirded out by it as well.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Thanks for understanding.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Nevertheless, I still intend to give this body back to Rapi ASAP, so don't worry about that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Hey, how could you say that? Rapi wouldn't be too happy hearing that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: And it was you who told me to get your oh-so-precious Rapi back to you as soon as possible.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: There's a time for joking around, and there's a time to be serious.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Red Hood and I continue to discuss the intricacies of emotions for a while.
I'm curious:
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Is Rapunzel still fixated on... you know what?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: I'm not sure what you're alluding to.
More than ever.
... Handsome.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Stop pretending.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: You know what I'm talking about. When a man and a woman... you know...
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Er...
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Some things never change.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: On that note,
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: any interesting new books on that particular subject?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: I'd like some recommendations... Uh, I mean...!
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Red Hood becomes bashful and clams up for a while.
Say,
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: is our favorite swordsman still living life to the hilt?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Very much so, all with the help of alcohol.
Maybe? Not sure.
Ha, good grief.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: It sometimes looks like she's more of a professional boozer than a swordsman.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Just be sure to check in with her once in a while. Don't let her spiral into addiction.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: It seems you don't know too much about her whereabouts.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: So she's still a bona fide walkabout?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Fair enough. That way of life suits her well.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Talked about Scarlet with Red Hood for a while.
How's my buddy, Snow White?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Is she still as adorable as before?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Utterly irresistible.
The relationship between you two is... rather unusual.
Ha, she really is, isn't she?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: I'm going to tell you something that I haven't told anyone else.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: There's no better feeling than getting her in a solid headlock with only one arm.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Her reaction is simply adorable.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Huh? What's so strange about it?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: She's as cute as a button! No one can deny that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Oh, you know what? There was this one time...
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Red Hood goes on to tell various stories about Snow White, but it feels like she is describing a completely different person.
Tell me something.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Do you ask a different Nikke out every day?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Yeah.
Not necessarily.
Oh, so you just pick the Nikke you want?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: And you switch it up each day?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: I never realized that before. You're kinda creepy.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: I guess that's one of the privileges of being a commander. I'm so jealous!
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: So how do you decide who to go with?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: I can't tell you the details.
Oh? Sounds awfully suspicious to me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: I think you just pick whichever Nikke you're jonesing after and ask them out.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: That way you can satisfy your base desires and have your way with them, am I right?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Red Hood teases me for quite some time with a rakish grin on her face.
I hope Dorothy
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: doesn't step out of line.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: I'll do my best to persuade her whenever I can.
Bit late for that, isn't it?
I knew I could count on you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Thanks, Handsome.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: I hope you can continue to look after her on my behalf.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Mmm...
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: I suppose you're right.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Things do seem to have reached the point of no return.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: *Sigh* What a mess.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Red Hood and I discuss Dorothy for a while.
Hey,
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: guess who made this weapon I'm using?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Dorothy?
Snow White?
Pssh, are you kidding?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: The lady who's always bloviating about how "barbaric"
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: it is to fight with your hands?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: You think she, of all people, would craft a weapon with her own hands? You should tell that joke to any Raptures we pass by. They'll die of laughter.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Correct yet again. Maybe that was a softball.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: I still remember her face when I asked her to make me an automatic drill.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: She had no idea what I was talking about. Completely dumbfounded.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: It was adorable. Haha.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Red Hood and I discuss weapons for a while.
You wanna know what the first book I gave Rapunzel was called?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Blinding Passion.
Eager & Insatiable.
What the...?!
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: How in the world did you guess that?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: You must be an avid collector of this kind of material.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: What the...?!
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: There's a book called that? That's a heck of a title. Very promising.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: What's it about? Tell me!
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Out with it!
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Red Hood and I discuss adult books for a while.
Red Hood is listening to her cassette player, as she usually does.
I love the sense of ceremony that comes with listening to music on a cassette recorder.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Don't you agree?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: It's more convenient with a cellphone.
I prefer vinyl records.
Ugh, you're such a philistine.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: The audio would be way too sterile if you play it over a cellphone.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: It ruins the fun and thrill of listening to music.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Wow, no kidding?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: I didn't realize you were so refined.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: You remind of me Dorothy, haha.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Discussed music with Red Hood for a while.
Whenever I see rabble-rousers or people with glasses,
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: I'm already reminded of Scarlet and Dorothy as they used to be.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Did they fight a lot?
Did they get along?
Their feuding was the stuff of legend.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: They'd spend entire days finding new ways to push each other's buttons.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: I'd watch them, engrossed entirely, and hours would pass by without me even noticing, ha.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Has anyone ever told you that you have no clue how to read the room?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: No.
I somehow seriously doubt that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Chatted with Red Hood for a while.
Hey, guess what I'm describing:
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: It's white and supple, and feels tender to the touch.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Cotton?
Snow?
Sorry, wrong answer.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: It's Snow White when she's sleeping.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: *Sigh*
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Gosh, I miss her more than anything.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Close, but no cigar.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: It's Snow White when she's sleeping.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Every once in a while, I find myself thinking about her.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: I really do miss her more than anything.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Red Hood and I absent-mindedly stare up at the sky for a while.
You may find this hard to believe,
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: but Dorothy had a cute side to her as well.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Quit pulling my leg.
Are we thinking of the same Dorothy?
I'm not joking. I mean it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: For example, how mad she'd get if you called her "Snooty",
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: or the way she pretended to be indifferent about something, when everyone else could clearly see how upset she was.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Actually...
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Now that I think about it, maybe those can't really be filed under "cute".
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Of course we are!
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: There's only one true fair lady, and that's our dear Snooty Dorothy.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: She looks radically different from how she did in the past,
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: so I can't blame you finding it hard to imagine another side of her.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Red Hood tells me more about how Dorothy differed in the past.
Hello, Commander.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Long time no see.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: ... Rapi?
Red Hood, are you trying to sound like Rapi?
Hey, come on, Handsome,
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: no need to look so down in the dumps.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: I was only playing a little practical joke.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Chin up, okay?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Ha, darn!
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: You saw right through me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: You really live up to that commander title.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: I'm impressed.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: I suddenly find myself missing Rapi more than ever.
What do you think about old antiques,
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: like this cassette player, for instance?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: I think they're cool.
I think they're old.
Not a bad answer,
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Handsome!
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: I've always preferred things with a history as well.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Bah. What a boring answer.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: It's an antique. Of course it's going to be old.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Red Hood and I exchange our opinions on antiques.
What's your stance on past achievements?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Do you think they have any real meaning?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: I think they hold a lot of value.
I think their value is limited.
I see.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: But isn't it a bit of a shame if someone rests on their laurels
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: and is unable to move on?
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: I wish there was a way I could get that through Dorothy's head.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Haha, I see.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Personally, I think you're right. The past is the past.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: We need to live in the present.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Right now, at this very moment, the future is barreling towards us,
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: and that makes it all the more vital, certainly much more so than the past.
adviseScripts.speaker: Red Hood

adviseScripts.text: Red Hood and I have a deep and meaningful conversation.
